==English==

===Etymology===
Short for the original phrase ''co-educational'' refering to an educational institution that taught males and females together.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[coed]].

===Adjective===
'''co--ed'''
# (''US'')An educational institution that teaches both males and females.
# (''US'')Any location that mixes males and females.

====Translations====
*French: [[mixte]]

===Noun===
'''co-ed'''
# (''US, dated'') A young woman who attends college.
# (''US'') A (generally young) woman, especially on the campus of a college or other educational institute.

